# ===== Pilot-Daten / VPS-Snapshots =====
# JSONL-Logs der Piloten enthalten kompletten Flight-Snapshot-Stream + PII.
# DB-Snapshots enthalten bcrypt-Hashes (provisioned_pilots, admin_users).
# Diese Files NIE committen — auch nicht "anonymisiert ohne ausdruecklich
# zu pruefen welche Felder PII tragen".
pilot-pirep-data-*.zip
pilot-pirep-data-*.tar.gz
aeroacars-live-snapshot-*.db
aeroacars-live-snapshot-*.db.gz
.release-notes-*.md

# ===== macOS code-signing / notarization =====
*.cer
*.p8
*.mobileprovision
notarize-output.txt

# ===== Tauri updater signing keys =====
# Private key NEVER commits — needed to sign releases. Public key DOES commit (in tauri.conf.json).
client/aeroacars-updater.key
client/aeroacars-updater.key.pub

# Local reverse-engineering / vendor reference assets — never push.
reference/
.research/

# ===== Release-Notes-Drafts =====
# Per-release bilingual notes go to GitHub via `gh release create --notes-file`.
# We don't need them in git — the canonical record is the GitHub release page
# plus the CHANGELOG.md.
.release-notes-*.md

# ===== TypeScript incremental build cache =====
# Auto-generated by `tsc -b`, machine-local, churns on every build.
*.tsbuildinfo

# Flug-Korpus-Export (Produktionsdaten, read-only Analyse) — nie einchecken
corpus-arrivals.csv
